etermines who can use an item and assigns each person a number. You get bonus points for each raid you go on, so your chances of winning increase the more raids you do. I had basically a 1 in 65 chance of winning an uber mask that was 15 wisdom and intelligence. All in all it was an interesting experience. I didn't get any experience or loot in fact I lost some of both. I will probably go on more raids. I felt kind of useless and stupid on this first one. All I did was get lost and fall into a pit. I need to redeem myself. Well I did pass out drinks to all who wanted to celebrate. There was plenty or Brell's beer to go around! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uopusorcharmer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Opus Orcharmer</A> at: 10/12/01 11:38:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uopusorcharmer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Opus Orcharmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(10/17/01 3:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nine's First Dragon Raid</span><hr size=1> I also want to thank Chance for going with me and helping me on this raid. Also, for pulling MOBs night after night so I could level. Your a good person and I am glad your in the guild despite what Ziag says. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uopusorcharmer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Opus Orcharmer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#8A2BE2>(10/24/01 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&in